\title{SAINT}
\description{
SAINT (Self-Attention and Intersample Attention Transformer) for tabular data.

Numeric features are embedded with a per-feature MLP, categorical features with an embedding
table, and a learned \code{CLS} token is prepended to the token sequence.
A transformer then applies attention \emph{across features} (like a standard tabular transformer) and
-- this is SAINT's key idea -- \emph{across the rows of a batch} ("intersample attention"), which lets
a row borrow information from other rows.
The \code{CLS} token of the last layer is passed through a two-layer MLP to obtain the prediction.

This is a port of the supervised path of the official implementation
(\url{https://github.com/somepago/saint}, Apache-2.0). The self-supervised pre-training stage of the
paper (contrastive + denoising losses, CutMix / mixup augmentation) is \strong{not} implemented.
}
